               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. SIMPSON</hi> 
                  <hi rend="italic">conducted the Prosecution.</hi>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18480821-name-634" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18480821-name-634" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18480821-name-634" type="surname" value="CURTAIN"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18480821-name-634" type="given" value="MARY"></interp>MARY CURTAIN</persName>
                  </hi>. I was out of service, and lived with my father, James Curtain, at Stevens'-place, Somers' Town. On Sunday, 23rd July, at six or seven o'clock in the morning, the prisoner and several men came and had some ginger-beer and coffee—he did not pay for it, but came up to me, put his hand into my pocket, broke the string of it, and left the house with it—there was a half-crown in it, there was 9<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. or 10<hi rend="italic">s</hi>., and 2<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. or 3<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. in copper—he returned in a quarter of an hour with some more men, and I gave him in charge.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined by</hi> 
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. METCALFE</hi>. <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> Had he had any gin? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> No—he had been there about half an hour—I served nothing but ginger-beer and coffee—there was another female there, but I took the money for everything.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18480821-name-635" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18480821-name-635" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18480821-name-635" type="surname" value="TAYLOR"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18480821-name-635" type="given" value="AMELIA"></interp>AMELIA TAYLOR</persName>
                  </hi>. I saw the prisoner come in and have some coffee, and saw him pull off Curtain's pocket and run out of the house.</p>
